INSERT INTO `course` VALUES (1,1,'We offer the lowest price in Australia for Professional Year','','<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/files/upload/images/py%20natti/1416697721.jpg\" style=\"height:189px; width:244px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We offered the lowest price course of Prfessional Year (Accounting)&nbsp;in Australia</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Century 21 Student Service Centre releases excellent courses to plus points for skilled independent migration pathway:</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>1. Professional Year</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Course Introduction</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Professional Year manages at least 44-week training course including</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Vocational Training:&nbsp;</strong>This subject will improve your conversation skills aspects of the workplace, interview skills, resume guidance, meeting procedures, commercial arrangements and other workplace knowledge of the subject.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Australia Workplace Concept:</strong>&nbsp;Undergraduate purpose of the design is to enable international students to the work ethic of Australians, for example: occupational health and safety division of labor among colleagues, to achieve the work plan, employee self-management, employee relations and how to solve problems at work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Professional Knowledge:</strong>&nbsp;This subject will be made for the development of students&#39; knowledge and skills to enable students to become professionals in related industries. These professional knowledge and work are closely linked, such as students learn accounting, you need to learn a lot in school no contact software, this expertise is very strong practical</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Professional Practice:&nbsp;</strong>This is the last and most crucial part of the course, the subjects will arrange students without payment into a regular company for 12 weeks internship opportunities for students to take this opportunity to develop their talents, which is the entire course of the most critical part. You must first interview by the school.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Professional project:&nbsp;</strong>the development of this subject will be made for the students&#39; knowledge and skills to enable students to become professionals in related industries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Professional Year Course aims primarily at students in the following skills</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Interview Capability - Provide formal resume format, in a simulated interview scene several times, the correct response interview questions; written communication skills - the ability to write formal business letters</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Teamwork Capability &ndash; Social Communication and ability to adapt to cultural differences</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Business Capability &ndash; Understand and comply with Australia&rsquo;s workplace code of practice, corporate culture and rule of ethics</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition, the school will also arrange business seminars organized by the Ministry of Personnel staff to student suggestions about their own personal experiences.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Where students in Australia completed a bachelor&#39;s degree or master&#39;s degree in school success, as the profession is accounting, IT or engineering, when after graduation the student that cannot reach migration standard as no related working experience can admit year professional Year (specialty) courses, complete this professional Year program, skill independent migration can be eligible for five points plus to successfully achieve immigration goals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Entry Requirement</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Applicant holding Graduate visa (subclass 485), or bridging visa A/B, or higher student visa subclass 573, or vice applicant for visa subclass 457, or PR</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Applicant with accounting profession should submit primary skill assessment, engineering profession should submit complete skill assessment, and no need of skill assessment for IT profession applicant</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. IELTS should get score 6 for each band and applicant should complete 2-year degree course</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Courses Released:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Accounting</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Computer Science</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Engineering</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Our Service</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Century 21 Student Service Centre can apply all colleges with Professional Year course in Sydney and provide students various kinds of choices</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Century 21 Student Service Centre is professional in applying scholarship for students, and most of applicants have obtained (AU$2000-AU$3000) high scholarship</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Century 21 Student Service Centre offers students applying accounting PY course through our company a gift including cash of AU$1000 or IPhone 6</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, most of our students in our company have been employed by excellent employer when finished PY course, which reach the target of both migration and employing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Course Advantage</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>5-point plus for skilled migration pathway (only Accounting, Engineering and IT for now)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students with no IELTS 7 for each band can also lodge skill assessment to CA for Accounting&nbsp;if applicant&nbsp;finishes PY course</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students with IT profession should finish PY course and then apply for skill assessment to get qualification of ACS in order to skill migration</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Graduate with outstanding performance may be employed by Internship Company</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tuition Fee: AUD$6,500 &ndash; AUD$13,000 (we offer great discount now, it is from<strong><span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"> AUD$5,700</span></span></strong>&nbsp;for Professional Year&nbsp;in Accounting)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Period: 44 weeks (including 12-week practice internship)</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n',0),(2,1,'We offer the lowest price in Australia for NAATI Course','','<h2><img alt=\"\" src=\"/files/upload/images/py%20natti/1416701452.jpg\" style=\"height:197px; width:272px\" /></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We offered the lowest price course of&nbsp;NAATI in Australia</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Century 21 Student Service Centre releases excellent courses to plus points for skilled independent migration pathway:</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>NAATI</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Course Introduction</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Full name of NAATI is National Accreditation Authority for Translators and Interpreters, headquartered in the capital Canberra. It is an internationally recognized accreditation agency interpreters and translators in the world, also with great reputation. NAATI with the Chinese translation of related courses including translation and interpretation category two tracks at the same time, both two directions from English to Chinese and Chinese to English, the level is divided into one to five with one is minimum and five is maximum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Australia, when most of the government agencies and private companies hire translator, employers are required to have at least three qualified translations, three, four and five are the Translation Bureau recognized professional translation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NAATI accreditation in the translation industry has a high qualified level, and the examination involved includes science and technology, life, medical, industrial and agricultural, financial, environmental, legal and other aspects. Three interpretation qualification exam is formed by the dialogue, test translations and consecutive interpreting as three major components.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To get the community language in Australia skilled migration five points plus, applicant must reach the translator level three or level two interpreter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When it comes to translation direction for the NAATI course, it is more general for native Chinese students to translate from English to Chinese.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Our Service</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Century 21 now offers special NAATI Course with <span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>AUD$4,900</strong></span></span> (AUD$6,200 originally) including all material fee and enrollment fee</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Century 21 Student Service Centre can apply all colleges with National Accreditation Authority for Translators and Interpreters course in Sydney and provide students various kinds of choices</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Century 21 Student Service Centre will recommend reasonable and best college for students based on individual information and requirement</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Course Advantage</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>5-point plus for skilled migration pathway</p>\r\n\r\n<p>when most of the government agencies and private companies hire translator, employers are required to have at least three qualified translations, three, four and five are the Translation Bureau recognized professional translation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students can efficiently improve their English speaking and reading skill during NAATI course study process, which also has benefit for IELTS test improvement. In this case, students can both get 5-point plus for skilled migration pathway and get IELTS 7 for each band for 10-point plus.</p>\r\n',0),(3,1,'TAFE WSI Courses','http://wsi.tafensw.edu.au/','<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>Uni and/or Career Pathway Examples</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fast-forward your career and/or higher education qualifications.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At TAFE Western Sydney we offer you flexibility. Choosing to study at TAFE before university &nbsp;is an economical and practical option. It enables you to graduate and enter the workforce with a competitive edge sooner. There are more pathways to choose from than listed here.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Animal Science</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Certificate II</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Animal Studies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Certificate III</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Animal Studies</li>\r\n	<li>Animal Technology</li>\r\n	<li>Captive Animals</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Certificate IV</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Veterinary Nursing</li>\r\n	<li>Captive Animals</li>\r\n	<li>Companion Animal Services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Diploma</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Animal Technology</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Bachelor Degree Pathways</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Many of our current Diploma course provide a credit pathway to University Degree programs or guaranteed direct entry.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Horse Courses</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Certificate II</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Racing (Stablehands - Harness &amp; Thoroughbred)</li>\r\n	<li>Racing Services (Administration)</li>\r\n	<li>Horse Industry Operations</li>\r\n	<li>Racing Services (track maintenance)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Certificate III - trades level workders</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Racing&nbsp;(Adv. Stablehand)</li>\r\n	<li>Racing Services (Cadet Steward)</li>\r\n	<li>Racing (Trackrider), Horse Industry Practice</li>\r\n	<li>Racing Services (Racing Administration)</li>\r\n	<li>Racing Services (Cadet Steward)</li>\r\n	<li>Racing Services (Track Maintenance)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Certificate IV</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Racing (Jockey)</li>\r\n	<li>Racking (Racehorse Trainer)</li>\r\n	<li>Racing Services (Racing Administration)</li>\r\n	<li>Racing Services (Track Maintenance)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Diploma</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Horse Industry Management (Performance Horse)</li>\r\n	<li>Racing Services (Track Management)</li>\r\n	<li>Racing Services (Administration or Steward)</li>\r\n	<li>Racehorse Trainer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Bachelor Degree Pathways</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Many of our current Diploma course provide a credit pathway to University Degree programs or guaranteed direct entry.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Environment &amp; The Land Courses</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Certificate II</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Agriculture</li>\r\n	<li>Arboriculture</li>\r\n	<li>Conservation &amp; Land Management</li>\r\n	<li>Horticulture</li>\r\n	<li>Production Horticulture</li>\r\n	<li>Production Nursery Retail Nursery</li>\r\n	<li>Landscaping</li>\r\n	<li>Parks &amp; Gardens</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Certificate III - trades level workers</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Agriculture</li>\r\n	<li>Arboriculture</li>\r\n	<li>Conservation &amp; Land Management</li>\r\n	<li>Indigenous Land Management</li>\r\n	<li>Horticulture</li>\r\n	<li>Production Horticulture</li>\r\n	<li>Production Nursery Retail Nursery</li>\r\n	<li>Landscape Construction</li>\r\n	<li>Parks &amp; Gardens</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Certificate IV - (higher trades &amp; para professional)</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Conservation&nbsp;&amp; Land Management</li>\r\n	<li>Horticulture</li>\r\n	<li>Production Horticulture</li>\r\n	<li>Production Nursery</li>\r\n	<li>Parks &amp; Gardens&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Diploma - (Professional level)</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Agriculture</li>\r\n	<li>Arboriculture</li>\r\n	<li>Conservation &amp; Land Management</li>\r\n	<li>Horticulture</li>\r\n	<li>Parks &amp; Gardens</li>\r\n	<li>Landsacpe Design</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Advanced Diploma</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Agriculture</li>\r\n	<li>Agribusiness</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Bachelor Degree Pathways</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Many of our current Diploma course provide a credit pathway to University Degree programs or guaranteed direct entry.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1),(4,1,'SIBN College Course Information','','<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong><u>Certificate III in Business [BSB30112] - Cricos Code: 081873B</u></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students who gain this qualification can further their study in the Certificate IV in Business BSB40212 or other Certificate IV qualifications or employment as customer service adviser, payroll officer, general clerk, word processing operator, typist or data entry operator.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong><u>Entry Requirements</u></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The target group for the Certificate III in Business BSB30112 is for those woh have completed HSC Year 11 or equivalent and want to develop the knowledge and skills to pursue emplyment in a wide range of business contexts across industry sectors. Applicants must have minimum age of 18 or over and have an intermediate English level or IEKLS 5.0 or equivalent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong><u>Course Duration</u></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The program is delivered over 4 terms (400 hours) and each term consist of 5 weeks. The program consists of 20 weeks of training with at least a minimum of 20 hours face-to-face training and 6 weeks of term break (Total 26 weeks).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Modes of Study</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the modes of study used at SIBN College include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tutorial group discussions</li>\r\n	<li>Lectures</li>\r\n	<li>Group work</li>\r\n	<li>Audio or visual presentations</li>\r\n	<li>Self-directed learning through research</li>\r\n	<li>Problem-solving</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><u><strong><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Assessment Methods</span></strong></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This course includes a variety of assessment methods including:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Practical demonstration / Observation</li>\r\n	<li>Questioning</li>\r\n	<li>Interview</li>\r\n	<li>Case study/Scenario Problem solving</li>\r\n	<li>Role play</li>\r\n	<li>Assignment</li>\r\n	<li>Written test/Knowledge Test</li>\r\n	<li>Report</li>\r\n	<li>Assignments</li>\r\n	<li>Portfolio</li>\r\n	<li>Short Q&amp;A</li>\r\n	<li>Project</li>\r\n	<li>Presentations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><strong>Certificate IV in Business - CRICOS Course Code: 081874A</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students who gain this qualification can further their study in a range of Diploma level qualifications within the BSB07 Business Services Training Package, or other Training Packages or employment as a Project Officer or Administration Officer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Entry Requirements</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The target goup for the Certificate IV in Business BSB40212 is for those who have completed HSC Year 12 or equivalent. Applicants must have minimum age of 18 or over and have an Upper intermediate English level or IELTS 5.5 or equivalent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Course Duration</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The program is delivered over 24 weeks or 480 hours or 3 terms and each term consists of 8 weeks (24 weeks of active learning with 20 hours weekly face to fce training plus 2 weeks term breaks = a total of 520 hours or 26 weeks).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Modes of study</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the modes of study used at SIBN College include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tutorial group discussions</li>\r\n	<li>Lectures</li>\r\n	<li>Group work</li>\r\n	<li>Audio or visual presentations</li>\r\n	<li>Self-directed learning through research</li>\r\n	<li>Problem-solving</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Assessment Methods</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This course includes a variety of assessment methods including:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Practical demonstration / Observation</li>\r\n	<li>Questioning</li>\r\n	<li>Interview</li>\r\n	<li>Case study/Scenario Problem solving</li>\r\n	<li>Role play</li>\r\n	<li>Assignment</li>\r\n	<li>Written test/Knowledge Test</li>\r\n	<li>Report</li>\r\n	<li>Assignments</li>\r\n	<li>Portfolio</li>\r\n	<li>Short Q&amp;A</li>\r\n	<li>Project</li>\r\n	<li>Presentations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><strong>Diploma of Marketing - CRICOS Course Code: 081875M</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students who gain this qualification can further their study in the Advanced Diploma of Marketing or other Advanced Diploma qualifications or employment as Marketing Manager, Marketing Team Leader, Product Manager or Public Relations Manager</p>\r\n\r\n<p><u><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Entry Requirements</strong></span></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:verdana,geneva,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\">The target group for the Diploma of Marketing BSB51207 is for those who have completed HSC Year 12 or equivalent and want to develop the knowledge and skills to work in marketing management, with managerial responsibility to ensure marketing functions are conducted effectively. Applicants must have minimum age of 18 or over and have an Upper intermediate English level or IELTS 5.5 or equivalent.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Course Duration</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\">The program is delivered over 4 terms (400 hours) and each term consist of 5 weeks.&nbsp; The program consists of 20 weeks of training with at least a minimum of 20 hours face-to-face training and 6 weeks of term break (Total 26 weeks).</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Modes of study</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the modes of study used at SIBN College include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tutorial group discussions</li>\r\n	<li>Lectures</li>\r\n	<li>Group work</li>\r\n	<li>Audio or visual presentations</li>\r\n	<li>Self-directed learning through research</li>\r\n	<li>Problem-solving</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Assessment Methods</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This course includes a variety of assessment methods including:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Practical demonstration / Observation</li>\r\n	<li>Questioning</li>\r\n	<li>Interview</li>\r\n	<li>Case study/Scenario Problem solving</li>\r\n	<li>Role play</li>\r\n	<li>Assignment</li>\r\n	<li>Written test/Knowledge Test</li>\r\n	<li>Report</li>\r\n	<li>Assignments</li>\r\n	<li>Portfolio</li>\r\n	<li>Short Q&amp;A</li>\r\n	<li>Project</li>\r\n	<li>Presentations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><strong>Advanced Diploma of Marketing - CRICOS Course Code: 081876K</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">Students who gain this qualification can gain employment as Marketing Director, Marketing Strategist or National/Regional/Global Marketing Manager.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Entry Requirements</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">The target group for the Advanced Diploma of Marketing BSB60507 is for those who have completed HSC Year 12 or equivalent and want to develop the knowledge and skills to provide leadership or strategic direction for the marketing activities of an organization. Applicants must have minimum age of 18 or over and have an Upper intermediate English level or IELTS 5.5 or equivalent.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Course Duration</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">The program is delivered over 4 terms (400 hours) and each term consist of 5 weeks. The program consists of 20 weeks of training with at least a minimum of 20 hours face-to-face training and 6 weeks of term break (Total 26 weeks).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Modes of study</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the modes of study used at SIBN College include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tutorial group discussions</li>\r\n	<li>Lectures</li>\r\n	<li>Group work</li>\r\n	<li>Audio or visual presentations</li>\r\n	<li>Self-directed learning through research</li>\r\n	<li>Problem-solving</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Assessment Methods</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This course includes a variety of assessment methods including:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Practical demonstration / Observation</li>\r\n	<li>Questioning</li>\r\n	<li>Interview</li>\r\n	<li>Case study/Scenario Problem solving</li>\r\n	<li>Role play</li>\r\n	<li>Assignment</li>\r\n	<li>Written test/Knowledge Test</li>\r\n	<li>Report</li>\r\n	<li>Assignments</li>\r\n	<li>Portfolio</li>\r\n	<li>Short Q&amp;A</li>\r\n	<li>Project</li>\r\n	<li>Presentations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><strong>Diploma of Management - CRICOS Course Code: 072841G</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">This course is designed to provide training for those people who wish to develop skills and knowledge in managing people in the workplace, making decisions or to add value or to review management practices. They are employable in any industry or organisational setting by focusing on the financial aspects of the organization. Typically people in these roles will have considerable experience in their respective industries or vocational areas and couple an informed perspective of the specific work requirements with their managerial approaches. Students who gain this qualification can further their study in the Advanced Diploma of Management</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Career Opportunities</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">Students who gain this qualification can further their study in the Advanced Diploma of Management (BSB60407) or other Advanced Diploma qualifications or employment as an Assistant Manager or Supervisor.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Entry Requirements</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">The target group for the Diploma of Management BSB51107 is for those who have completed HSC Year 12 or equivalent and want to develop the knowledge and skills to work in management across a range of business and organisational settings. Applicants must have minimum age of 18 or over and have an Upper intermediate English level or IELTS 5.5 or equivalent.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Course Duration</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">The program is delivered over 3 terms (480 hours) and each term consist of 8 weeks. The program consists of 24 weeks of training with at least a minimum of 20 hours face-to-face training and 2 weeks of term break.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Modes of study</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the modes of study used at SIBN College include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tutorial group discussions</li>\r\n	<li>Lectures</li>\r\n	<li>Group work</li>\r\n	<li>Audio or visual presentations</li>\r\n	<li>Self-directed learning through research</li>\r\n	<li>Problem-solving</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Assessment Methods</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This course includes a variety of assessment methods including:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Practical demonstration / Observation</li>\r\n	<li>Questioning</li>\r\n	<li>Interview</li>\r\n	<li>Case study</li>\r\n	<li>Role play</li>\r\n	<li>Assignment</li>\r\n	<li>Written test</li>\r\n	<li>Report</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><strong>Advanced Diploma of Management - CRICOS Course Code: 072842F</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">This course is designed to provide training for those people who wish to develop skills and knowledge in managing people in the workplace and making decisions by focusing on the various aspects of management in the organization. This course enables the learner to assume senior or managerial responsibilities in the organisation. They may oversee the work of others or have specialised roles where they do not supervise others but provide strategic leadership.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Career Opportunities</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">Students who gain this qualification may choose to undertake studies at higher education level and/or after having this qualification the students can gain employment as a Manager.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Entry Requirements</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">The target group for the Advanced Diploma of Management BSB60407 is for those who have completed HSC Year 12 or equivalent and want to develop the knowledge and skills to work in senior or strategic management across a range of business and organisational settings. Applicants must have minimum age of 18 or over and have an Upper intermediate English level or IELTS 5.5 or equivalent.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Course Duration</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">Duration:The program is delivered over 24 weeks or&nbsp; 480 hours or 3 terms and each term consist of 8 weeks (24 weeks of active learning with 20 hours weekly face to face training&nbsp; plus 2 weeks term breaks = a total of 520 hours or 26 weeks).</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Modes of study</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the modes of study used at SIBN College include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Practical demonstration / Observation</li>\r\n	<li>Questioning</li>\r\n	<li>Interview</li>\r\n	<li>Case study/Scenario Problem solving</li>\r\n	<li>Role play</li>\r\n	<li>Assignment</li>\r\n	<li>Written test/Knowledge Test</li>\r\n	<li>Report</li>\r\n	<li>Assignments</li>\r\n	<li>Portfolio</li>\r\n	<li>Short Q&amp;A</li>\r\n	<li>Project</li>\r\n	<li>Presentations</li>\r\n	<li>Problem-solving</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Assessment Methods</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This course includes a variety of assessment methods including:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Practical demonstration / Observation</li>\r\n	<li>Questioning</li>\r\n	<li>Interview</li>\r\n	<li>Case study</li>\r\n	<li>Role play</li>\r\n	<li>Assignment</li>\r\n	<li>Written test</li>\r\n	<li>Report</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><strong>Certificate IV in Accounting - CRICOS Course Code: 081877J</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">Students who gain this qualification can further their study in the Diploma of Accounting (FNS50210). The course also prepares the students for work such as Assistant accountant, junior Auditor, Accounting Clerk, Costing clerk, Asset and inventory clerk, Assistant in budget operation etc.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Entry Requirements</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">Preferred pathways for candidates entering this qualification include Certificate III in Accounts Administration (FNS30310) or for those who have completed HSC Year 12 or equivalent. Applicants must have minimum age of 18 or over and have an Upper intermediate English level or IELTS 5.5 or equivalent.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong><span style=\"color:#000000\">Course Duration</span></strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">The program is delivered over 6 terms (30weeks X 20 hours per week = 600 hours) and each term consist of 5 weeks. The program consists of 30 weeks of training with at least a minimum of 20 hours face-to-face training and 10 weeks of term break (600hours + 200hours = 800hours a total of 40 weeks).</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Modes of study</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the modes of study used at SIBN College include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tutorial group discussions</li>\r\n	<li>Lectures</li>\r\n	<li>Group work</li>\r\n	<li>Audio or visual presentations</li>\r\n	<li>Self-directed learning through research</li>\r\n	<li>Problem-solving</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Assessment Methods</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This course includes a variety of assessment methods including:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Practical demonstration / Observation</li>\r\n	<li>Questioning</li>\r\n	<li>Interview</li>\r\n	<li>Case study/Scenario Problem solving</li>\r\n	<li>Role play</li>\r\n	<li>Assignment</li>\r\n	<li>Written test/Knowledge Test</li>\r\n	<li>Report</li>\r\n	<li>Assignments</li>\r\n	<li>Portfolio</li>\r\n	<li>Short Q&amp;A</li>\r\n	<li>Project</li>\r\n	<li>Presentations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><strong>Diploma of Accouting - CRICOS Course Code: 081878G</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">Students who gain this qualification can further their study in the Advanced Diploma of Accounting (FNS60210). The course also prepares the students for work such as Assistant Auditor, Assistant Accountant, Bookkeeper, Budget Officer, Assistant in financial management projects, Internal control, costing project officer etc.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Entry Requirements</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">The entry requirement for this qualification is completion of the units which comprise the core from the Certificate IV in Accounting in the Financial Services Training Package FNS10. Applicants must have minimum age of 18 or over and have an Upper intermediate English level or IELTS 5.5 or equivalent.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Course Duration</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">The program is delivered over 5 terms (500 hours) and each term consist of 5 weeks. The program consists of 25 weeks of training with at least a minimum of 20 hours face-to-face training and 8 weeks of term break. (500hours + 160hours = 660hours; a total of 33 weeks).&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">Students who gain this qualification can further their study in the Advanced Diploma of Accounting (FNS60210). The course also prepares the students for work such as Assistant Auditor, Assistant Accountant, Bookkeeper, Budget Officer, Assistant in financial management projects, Internal control, costing project officer etc.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Modes of study</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the modes of study used at SIBN College include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tutorial group discussions</li>\r\n	<li>Lectures</li>\r\n	<li>Group work</li>\r\n	<li>Audio or visual presentations</li>\r\n	<li>Self-directed learning through research</li>\r\n	<li>Problem-solving</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Assessment Methods</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This course includes a variety of assessment methods including:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Practical demonstration / Observation</li>\r\n	<li>Questioning</li>\r\n	<li>Interview</li>\r\n	<li>Case study/Scenario Problem solving</li>\r\n	<li>Role play</li>\r\n	<li>Assignment</li>\r\n	<li>Written test/Knowledge Test</li>\r\n	<li>Report</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u><strong>Advanced Diploma of Accouting - CRICOS Course Code: 081879G</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">Students who gain this qualification can further their study in relevant higher education program. The course also prepares the students for work such as Auditor, Accountant, Finance manager, Management Accountant etc.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Entry Requirements</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">Preferred pathways for candidates entering this qualification include Diploma of Accounting (FNS50210) or for those who have completed HSC Year 12 or equivalent. Applicants must have minimum age of 18 or over and have an Upper intermediate English level or IELTS 5.5 or equivalent.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Course Duartion</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:lucida sans unicode,lucida grande,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">The program is delivered over 10 terms (500 hours) and each term consist of 5 weeks. The program consists of 25 weeks of training with at least a minimum of 20 hours face-to-face training and 8 weeks of term break. (500hours + 160hours = 660hours; a total of 33 weeks). Refer to Delivery Structure below.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Modes of study</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the modes of study used at SIBN College include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tutorial group discussions</li>\r\n	<li>Lectures</li>\r\n	<li>Group work</li>\r\n	<li>Audio or visual presentations</li>\r\n	<li>Self-directed learning through research</li>\r\n	<li>Problem-solving</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u><strong>Assessment Methods</strong></u></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This course includes a variety of assessment methods including:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Practical demonstration / Observation</li>\r\n	<li>Questioning</li>\r\n	<li>Interview</li>\r\n	<li>Case study/Scenario Problem solving</li>\r\n	<li>Role play</li>\r\n	<li>Assignment</li>\r\n	<li>Written test/Knowledge Test</li>\r\n	<li>Report</li>\r\n	<li>Assignments</li>\r\n	<li>Portfolio</li>\r\n	<li>Short Q&amp;A</li>\r\n	<li>Project</li>\r\n	<li>Presentations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1),(5,1,'Study and Earn Money in Hotel Business','HMI','<p><strong>Abstract</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dual qualification of Advanced Diploma in both&nbsp;Hospitality and Events</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Living in hotel with free accomodationfor half a year</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Earn money in workplace for one and half a year</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pathway to third year of university when finishing this course</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Only four years package including&nbsp;advanced diploma, bachelor and master degree</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/files/upload/images/HMI/12.jpg\" style=\"height:300px; width:600px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ABOUT HMI</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Hotel Management Institute (HMI) is a unique partnership between the Escarpment Group of Hotels and TAFE Western Sydney. The partnership brings together the expertise of Vocational Education and residential work placement conducted across the multi-award winning Escarpment Group properties that include Lilianfels Resort and Spa, Echoes Boutique Hotel and Restaurant, Parklands Country Garden &amp; Lodges and The Hydro Majestic Hotel; all of which are icons of the famous World Heritage Blue Mountains region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Escarpment Group properties are recognized nationally and internationally as the epitome of quality and service in the hotel industry. HMI students will be immersed in and surrounded by excellence in hotel operations whilst being nurtured and developed through TAFE Western Sydney - one of Australia&rsquo;s largest Vocational Education providers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HMI provides exciting career opportunities in the hotel and events industries in the Blue Mountains of NSW, Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>LIVE IN LUXURY</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the Hotel Management Institute students live in at the iconic Hydro Majestic Hotel (or at an alternative hotel within the Escarpment Group), experiencing the live hotel environment on a daily basis. Living and working in the hotel enables students to develop the essential skills required for today&rsquo;s workplaces.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/files/upload/images/HMI/live%20in%20luxury.jpg\" style=\"height:452px; width:692px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>BE WORK READY</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our program balances the need for theoretical study, technical skills and professional development to ensure our graduates are career ready and prepared for the highest levels of the industry. This holistic approach set within the live hotel environment ensures that knowledge and skills learned, are contextualized and applied in a real and current operational environment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>EARN WHILE YOU LEARN</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/files/upload/images/HMI/5.jpg\" style=\"height:454px; width:553px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students have the opportunity to obtain casual work at one the four Escarpment Group properties during their course, assisting financially and providing valuable work experience. All properties are within easy commuting distance to the Hydro Majestic Hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ENJOY A UNIQUE GLOBAL EXPERIENCE</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Let us help you prepare for a career in an increasingly international workforce. Take the opportunity to study with Australian students and classmates from around the world, improve your languages skills, learn about Australian culture and develop an extensive network of friends and experts in the industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At HMI, it focuses on giving you the practical skills, confidence and opportunities to achieve your goals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/files/upload/images/HMI/chair.jpg\" style=\"height:341px; width:600px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PATHWAYS TO SUCCESS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>2 Advanced Diplomas in 2 Years!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students will complete a dual qualification in two years at HMI, undertaking a fast tracked Advanced Diploma in both Hospitality and Events.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>+1 Year To A Degree</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HMI has established pathways to universities. After completing the HMI Advanced Diplomas, you can study for one more year at the University of Western Sydney to achieve a Bachelor of Business and Commerce or a Bachelor of Applied Management at Federation University of Australia via distance (domestic study only).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>+1 More Year To A Master&rsquo;s Degree</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Undertake a further year at University of Western Sydney to achieve a Master&rsquo;s degree (MBA &ndash; Hospitality and Tourism).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>STUDY AT HMI</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/files/upload/images/HMI/study%20at%20HMI.jpg\" style=\"height:464px; width:600px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>FEES AND EARNING CAPACITY</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/files/upload/images/HMI/fees.jpg\" style=\"height:259px; width:700px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Includes accommodation and all meals, printing, study guides, photocopying, email and internet access.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All figures are stated in AUD. Potential earning based on current Australian wage rates at the time of publication for up to 20 hours per week. Minimum wages outlined in the National Workplace Relations system are reviewed by Fair Work Australia annually. Figures are correct at time of publication but fees and earnings are subject to change.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students will be required to live independently for the final semester of the Advanced Diplomas and any further study for the approved pathways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/files/upload/images/HMI/HMI.jpg\" style=\"height:267px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>GET TO KNOW TAFE WESTERN SYDNEY</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The classroom training components are delivered through the multi-award winning TAFE Western Sydney. We provide high quality, progressive vocational training and workforce development services and higher education qualifications.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The aim is to enhance employment and further study opportunities for individuals and to improve the capability, productivity and sustainability of businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Its customized education and training solutions are developed in collaboration with enterprise, community and educational partners, and are underpinned by extensive analysis, research and design.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Blue Mountains College features an industry-standard training restaurants as well as the latest technologies and training facilities for massage and beauty therapy and outdoor recreation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>LOCATION INFORMATION</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/files/upload/images/HMI/locatioin%20info.jpg\" style=\"height:169px; width:700px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>HMI is located in the beautiful world heritage-listed Blue Mountains National Park. As one of Australia&rsquo;s leading tourist destinations with a steadily increasing population, hospitality, tourism and events are key regional industries, offering students great opportunities working in a hotel environment within a key tourism destination.</p>\r\n',-1);
